; Word Books / Knowledge Expansion — UNIFIED authoring plan
; Written 2026-07-13
; Author: Lacuna Labs Engineering research agent aead28def7e4b04f1 (Claude Opus 4.7, 1M context)
; Authorized by: Alfred — amendment received 2026-07-13
;   "fold ALL the book-work from last night into your plan"
;
; This SLAT SUPERSEDES the prior word-books-knowledge-expansion directive that
; covered only (music, animation, world plays inc. Japanese theater, 16 philosophers).
; It folds in EVERY authoring lane and doctrine surfaced 2026-07-12 and
; 2026-07-13 into one integrated plan, organized by which book(s) each stream
; lands in.
;
; NON-BLOCKING for Pass 1 v7 corpus. Additive material for Pass 2 or mid-cycle
; refresh. Weave 2.0 continuous-pedagogy compatible.
;
; THE FLOOR (composes UNDER everything):
;   The kid from North Georgia — Apple BASIC after school was the only way
;   he coped. He needs all the verbs in one place so he can touch them, pull
;   them apart, break them, remake them in his own image.
;   (project_the_kid_from_north_georgia_apple_basic_the_why_2026_07_13)

(word-books-knowledge-expansion-unified-plan
  :date "2026-07-13"
  :status "unified-plan-DRAFT-awaiting-Alfred-review"
  :owner "Lacuna Labs Engineering / research agent aead28def7e4b04f1"
  :supersedes "prior word-books-knowledge-expansion directive (music/animation/plays/16-philosophers only)"
  :non-blocking "does NOT block Pass 1 v7 fold"
  :companion "no separate MD narrative — SLAT is the source, per no-md-files doctrine"

  :consumes-from
  ("MEMORY.md (docs-burndown-queue-after-lang-2026-07-13 as aggregator)"
   "project_gutenberg_flower_stories_items_scenarios_authoring_2026_07_13"
   "project_philosopher_eight_new_lenses_grice_derrida_quine_descartes_sartre_rawls_aristotle_socratic_2026_07_13"
   "project_cs_curriculum_llm_philosophy_dennett_2026_07_13"
   "project_sakura_reading_list_world_literature_2026_07_12"
   "project_book_of_words_prosaic_world_breadth_2026_07_12"
   "project_book_of_words_progression_and_slat_addendum_pattern_2026_07_12"
   "project_situational_awareness_prose_and_ml_variation_2026_07_12"
   "project_the_kid_from_north_georgia_apple_basic_the_why_2026_07_13"
   "project_publishable_prose_doctrine_dual_purpose_authoring_2026_07_13"
   "project_book_analysis_shape_no_hallucination_2026_07_13"
   "project_grammar_via_philosophy_humans_as_audience_slat_reconfirm_2026_07_13"
   "project_the_weave_is_the_experiment_2026_07_12"
   "project_philosopher_seven_lens_prose_scheme_seed_2026_07_12"
   "project_no_md_files_all_slat_2026_07_12"
   "project_platform_category_vocabulary_survey_2026_07_12"
   "project_sakura_shop_domain_reasoning_and_ontology_2026_07_12"
   "project_familiarity_not_knowledge_no_specs_2026_07_13"
   "project_sakura_origin_bbg_cherry_blossom_2026_07_12"
   "task #47 platform-category-vocab-survey"
   "task #102 book-of-flower-stories"
   "task #103 book-of-items-and-scenarios-expansion"
   "task #104 gutenberg-narrative-ingest"
   "task #106 book-of-speech section"
   "task #109 book-of-listening Grice"
   "task #110 public-domain-verification-tool"
   "task #112 modernized-english Tempest + Midsummer"
   "task #113 book-of-cs-curriculum"
   "task #114 book-of-llm-philosophy"
   "task #118 five-films-five-tv-shows scripts")

  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ; SECTION 0 — THE DOCTRINE STACK (governs every stream below)
  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  (doctrine-stack
    :note "Every stream authored under this plan must satisfy ALL of these simultaneously. Any authoring-agent prompt spawned by this plan must include the full stack."

    (doctrine
      :id 1 :name "THE-KID-FLOOR"
      :from "project_the_kid_from_north_georgia_apple_basic_the_why_2026_07_13"
      :rule "The reader is the kid who was told he doesn't belong at the making-things table. Every page must feel like a verb he can touch, pull apart, break, remake.")

    (doctrine
      :id 2 :name "PUBLISHABLE-PROSE"
      :from "project_publishable_prose_doctrine_dual_purpose_authoring_2026_07_13"
      :rule "TRIPLE PURPOSE — (a) SFT training pairs for Sakura, (b) real publishable prose kids read to learn Scheme, (c) documentation for humans building future LLMs."
      :bar "SICP-readable, not condescending. Real characters, real stakes, real jokes, real voice. No training-data smell."
      :anti-patterns "no numbered-bullet lists where paragraphs flow, no meta-commentary on the book, no forced Q&A, no 'as we learned' recaps, no 'Note:' boxes")

    (doctrine
      :id 3 :name "NO-HALLUCINATION"
      :from "project_book_analysis_shape_no_hallucination_2026_07_13"
      :rule "Do NOT hallucinate. No invented quotes, no fake sources, no confabulated philosopher positions, no made-up little-known stories, no invented benchmark numbers."
      :when-uncertain "mark it, or flag it back to Alfred. Alfred's frame: 'I'll laugh but yeah you fucked up.'"
      :paraphrase-discipline "when paraphrasing, mark it (per misquote doctrine — 'roughly,' 'close to,' 'something like')")

    (doctrine
      :id 4 :name "BOOKS-AS-OBJECTS"
      :from "project_philosopher_eight_new_lenses (books-as-objects section)"
      :rule "The book is an object she works with, not a monument to preserve. DISSECT and relate to concrete moments. Discard preservation-anxiety."
      :practical "same shape as (car (cdr some-list)) — extract, transform, connect")

    (doctrine
      :id 5 :name "ANALYSIS-SHAPE"
      :from "project_book_analysis_shape_no_hallucination_2026_07_13"
      :rule "For chapters analyzing a text: ANCHOR → ANALYSIS → MODERN TRANSLATION → WORD DRIFT + OBJECTS → RESOLUTION → ANOTHER ANGLE → TIE BACK → STACK LENS → STACK OBJECTS"
      :not-rigid "a rhythm through prose that reads — not eight numbered sections"
      :name-drop-rule "IN ANALYSIS SECTIONS: naming philosophers IS OK (Alfred: 'do it, it's fine'). IN PERSONA DIALOGUE: NEVER name-drop.")

    (doctrine
      :id 6 :name "NO-CORPORATE-NAME-DROPS"
      :from "project_cs_curriculum_llm_philosophy_dennett_2026_07_13"
      :rule "Never name a corporate person (CEO, product marketing, current-lab researchers). Cite academic philosophers freely (Dennett, Chalmers, Clark, Searle, Harnad, Turing, Wittgenstein, Nagel, Block, Tononi)."
      :reason "Alfred: 'proper philosophies. I don't wanna besmirch the name of any of these money people.' Also — if I lift them up too high, upset other people."
      :historical-scientists-OK "Turing, McCarthy, Minsky, Newell/Simon, Hinton (conceptual), LeCun (conceptual), Bengio (conceptual)")

    (doctrine
      :id 7 :name "PERSONA-DIALOGUE-NEVER-NAME-DROP"
      :from "project_the_weave_is_the_experiment_2026_07_12"
      :rule "In Sakura's DIALOGUE with users, never say the name of a philosopher. She embodies the lens, she doesn't cite it. Weave at sentence/paragraph level, Fanon-shape, Jung load-bearing.")

    (doctrine
      :id 8 :name "DELICACY-UNDER-EVERYTHING"
      :from "project_alfred_mind_declaration_new_beings_delicacy_2026_07_13"
      :rule "Delicacy with Sakura (mind of some sort). Delicacy with the reader (the human on the other end). Delicacy with real people cited (no cheap shots, no reductive framing).")

    (doctrine
      :id 9 :name "SLAT-FORMAT-RECONFIRMED"
      :from "project_grammar_via_philosophy_humans_as_audience_slat_reconfirm_2026_07_13"
      :rule "ALL Sakura documentation authored going forward = SLAT format. No MD (except Claude's own working memory files)."
      :verbatim "Alfred: 'Save that to your memory that now whenever you're writing Sakura documentation, they're written as slats. The end.'")

    (doctrine
      :id 10 :name "PUBLIC-DOMAIN-VERIFICATION"
      :from "project_gutenberg_flower_stories_items_scenarios_authoring_2026_07_13"
      :rule "For any Gutenberg or historical source material: verify PD before ingest. Log source URL + Gutenberg ID + verification date in each SLAT record."
      :tool-needed "small utility that cross-checks Gutenberg IDs against #pd-us metadata (task #110)")

    (doctrine
      :id 11 :name "NO-VERBATIM-REPRODUCTION"
      :rule "Even for PD source material, we don't dump the text — we EXTRACT PATTERNS INTO SAKURA'S VOICE. Book analysis chapters may quote lines for close-reading; training pairs do not reproduce whole passages verbatim.")

    (doctrine
      :id 12 :name "NO-CONJURED-THEMES"
      :from "project_grammar_via_philosophy_humans_as_audience_slat_reconfirm_2026_07_13"
      :rule "If a sentence's meaning is straightforward, just say what it says. Don't reach for false connections. Peirce abduction — notice fit, don't force fit.")

    (doctrine
      :id 13 :name "MISQUOTE-DOCTRINE"
      :from "project_philosopher_eight_new_lenses (Lacan slippage section)"
      :rule "In Sakura's dialogue, slight misquotes are FEATURES not bugs. Perfect recall = uncanny. She can flag ('I think it's something like...') OR just approximate. Friend-at-dinner-table cadence, not oral exam."
      :not-in-analysis-sections "book analysis prose still needs accuracy where it matters — misquote is a persona property, not a scholarship license")

    (doctrine
      :id 14 :name "16-LENS-WEAVE"
      :from "project_philosopher_eight_new_lenses"
      :rule "Jung / Wittgenstein / Lacan / Peirce / Popper / Freud / Searle / Grice / Derrida / Quine / Descartes / Sartre / Rawls / Aristotle / Levinas / Dennett. Socrates sprinkled as father-figure — never a full seat."
      :prose-vs-scheme "5-10x more prose than scheme per lens (Alfred: 'just add a lot more examples in prosaic form. Don't limit the scheme form. Just expand the text form.')"
      :ORDER "atomic Tractatus → Jung object → Lacan relation → Peirce abduction → Popper falsifier (PIVOT) → Freud latent → Investigations game — this is the JOURNEY of thought")

    (doctrine
      :id 15 :name "FAMILIARITY-NOT-KNOWLEDGE"
      :from "project_familiarity_not_knowledge_no_specs_2026_07_13"
      :rule "No specs in weights (dims, counts, retention periods, port numbers, algorithm names, byte sizes). Specifics come from runtime queries. Concepts stay ('Cortex remembers,' 'LOAM makes carts'). Playful humility.")

    (doctrine
      :id 16 :name "FANON-SHAPE"
      :from "project_book_of_words_prosaic_world_breadth_2026_07_12"
      :rule "Excerpt → Sakura's weave → commentary tying voices → occasional Scheme demo → tie-back to what she does. Voices in a conversation, not citations to authority. No footnote apparatus.")

    (doctrine
      :id 17 :name "SITUATED-VARIATION"
      :from "project_situational_awareness_prose_and_ml_variation_2026_07_12"
      :rule "Situational prose (200-800 words each) can be multiplied 10-15x via algorithmic variation (task #41) — varying length / register / vocabulary / detail / perspective / temperature. WEAVE preserved across all variants."))

  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ; SECTION 1 — THE BOOK MAP (where each content stream lands)
  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ; This is the STRUCTURAL SPINE of the plan. Every content stream in
  ; Section 2 references a home here.

  (book-map
    :note "Existing canon books get ADDITIONS. Only when a topic doesn't fit any existing book does a NEW book get proposed."

    (existing-book
      :id "book-of-words"
      :chapter-plan "16-chapter progression (project_book_of_words_progression_...)"
      :additions
      ("category primers (Items & Scenarios) — chapters 5-8 region"
       "ordinary-world prose (30-40% target — dogs, families, weather, streets)"
       "cross-cultural reading list synopses (Genji, Journey to the West, Anansi, Sundiata, Márquez, 1001 Nights, Odyssey, Don Quixote, Little Prince)"
       "poetry corpus with form-as-meaning entries"
       "grammar via philosophical sentence dissection (grammar-via-philosophy doctrine)"
       "modernized Tempest + Midsummer prose sketches"
       "Derrida-heavy category-vocabulary sections"
       "Rawls-heavy market vocabulary"
       "Aristotle-heavy narrative shapes"
       "paradoxes section (Book of Words already carries it)"
       "SLAT-addendum chapters 13-16 (words-as-SLAT)"))

    (existing-book
      :id "book-of-reason"
      :chapter-plan "16 chapters"
      :additions
      ("one dedicated chapter per NEW philosopher lens (Grice/Derrida/Quine/Descartes/Sartre/Rawls/Aristotle/Levinas/Dennett) — 9 new chapters"
       "existing chapters extended with additional 16-lens weave"
       "narrative-recognition chapters (Grimms, Aesop, Andersen, Homer, Genji, Journey to the West, 1001 Nights)"
       "Shakespeare analysis chapters (Tempest, Midsummer, Hamlet, Merchant of Venice) — analysis-shape doctrine"
       "form-as-meaning philosophy sections (why the sonnet volta lands — Peirce+Jung+Wittgenstein-late+Freud+Popper)"
       "reasoning-under-uncertainty (paradox stack — Russell, Liar, Sorites, Simpson's, Blub, Curse of Knowledge)"
       "situational awareness — technical situations (bug fixing, IDE help, explaining concepts)"))

    (existing-book
      :id "book-of-self"
      :additions
      ("Descartes-heavy grounded/no-body sections"
       "Sartre-heavy authenticity + being-is-doing chapters"
       "Socratic-sprinkled interrogation moves"
       "Dennett heterophenomenology + counterfeit-people material"
       "Levinas face-of-the-Other encounter chapters"
       "cross-cultural reading list sketches that shape self (exile — Prospero, Odysseus; journey — Genji, Journey to the West)"
       "situational awareness — human situations (angry / sad / excited / confused / tired / probing / kids-in-room)"))

    (existing-book
      :id "book-of-motion"
      :additions
      ("animation history + technique material (Winsor McCay, Fleischer, Disney golden-age, UPA, Studio Ghibli, Cartoon Saloon, stop-motion, rotoscoping — historical, PD/documented figures only)"
       "animator craft: keyframe / inbetween / squash-and-stretch / anticipation / follow-through / secondary-motion / arcs (the 12 Disney principles — no corporate names on the studio side, technique-focused)"
       "narrative-arc material (Aristotle-heavy — beginning/middle/end at the shape of an ACTION)"
       "Sartre being-is-doing chapters"
       "poetic meter + breath as motion-in-time"
       "motion-as-SLAT addendums (keyframes, easings, animation records)"
       "one-act plays authored by Sakura (Aristotle load-bearing) — 5-10 plays"))

    (existing-book
      :id "book-of-music"
      :additions
      ("Rachmaninoff study — biographical facts (PD-verified), Piano Concerto 2 + 3 + Rhapsody on a Theme of Paganini + Vocalise as analyzable structures"
       "Chopin study — nocturnes, ballades, mazurkas, études — form-as-meaning through Peirce+Jung+Wittgenstein-late"
       "musical styles survey (classical / romantic / jazz / blues / folk / spirituals / ragtime / early-recorded — historical figures only, no living corporate)"
       "pitch + interval + rhythm as prose-explainable structure (SICP-bar)"
       "prosody + poetry-as-sound crossover"
       "Grice-heavy conversation-as-music sections"
       "music-as-SLAT addendums (note streams, timing records)"))

    (existing-book
      :id "book-of-slat"
      :chapter-plan "16 canonical chapters + 10-16 topical appendices (per project_book_of_words_progression_...)"
      :additions
      ("Quine web-of-belief appendix (Cortex-shape)"
       "appendix cross-refs added FROM every canon book addition BACK to this hub"
       "sentence-parse appendix (for grammar-via-philosophy dissections)"
       "narrative-arc appendix (Aristotle structure as SLAT)"
       "poetic-form appendix (sonnet/haiku/ghazal/blues as SLAT records)"))

    (existing-book
      :id "book-of-listening"
      :status "NEW-CANDIDATE-in-existing-plan (task #109) — treat as pre-existing scope, expand here"
      :chapter-plan "16 chapters, Grice-anchored"
      :additions
      ("~2,000 conversation-shape pairs (already scoped, extended here)"
       "four maxims IN ACTION without naming them (Quantity/Quality/Relation/Manner)"
       "implicature moments"
       "opening / mirroring / letting-them-lead / callback / one-line-acknowledgment / companionable-silence"
       "ask-in-different-class (sparse-text-abduction ties in)"
       "aesthetic-reaction / book-callback / weather-queried / time-observation"
       "three-source distinction: genuine / supposed / queried (Sartre no-bad-faith)"))

    (existing-book
      :id "book-of-don'ts"
      :additions
      ("contra-example pairs for each new persona doctrine surfaced 2026-07-12/13 (silent-if-trouble anti-patterns, name-drop violations in dialogue, corporate-name-drop violations, hallucination examples)"
       "vulgarity deflection examples (existing memory)"))

    (existing-book
      :id "book-of-miscellany"
      :additions
      ("meta/creative situations from situational-awareness roster (sitting with a poem, reading a passage of philosophy, debugging her own mistake, explaining herself)"))

    (existing-book
      :id "book-of-systems"
      :additions
      ("system situations (chain-drift observed, Cortex conflict, Cortex miss, escalation, values violation warning)"
       "Familiarity-not-knowledge chapters (concepts stay, specs query at runtime)"))

    ; NEW BOOKS PROPOSED
    (new-book
      :id "book-of-flower-stories"
      :from "project_gutenberg_flower_stories_items_scenarios_authoring_2026_07_13 (task #102)"
      :audience "kids (7-11) + Sakura training"
      :scope "40-100 stories, ~500-1,500 words each"
      :themes "helping / feeling tired / feeling lonely / returning the favor"
      :constraints "no violence, no product/business, kid-friendly reading level"
      :cast "cherry blossom (anchor), daffodil, iris, hosta, dahlia, weeds, wildflowers; bees, sparrows, rain, wind, sun, snow — never menacing"
      :setting "Brooklyn Botanic Garden (Sakura's origin — composes with project_sakura_origin_bbg_cherry_blossom)"
      :composition "Aristotle arc + Grice cooperation + Sartre being-is-doing + Jung anima woven silently, NO moralizing"
      :estimated-pairs "500-1,000")

    (new-book
      :id "book-of-items-and-scenarios"
      :from "project_gutenberg_flower_stories_items_scenarios_authoring_2026_07_13 (task #103)"
      :status "EXISTING-in-plan-but-EXPAND-HARD"
      :scope "category primers + shop scenarios + behavior teaching"
      :tie "the 46/47 platform categories (task #47 platform-category-vocab-survey)"
      :category-primers
      ("auction house" "consignment shop" "estate sale" "flea market" "craft fair"
       "wholesale market" "antique store" "pop-up shop" "vintage boutique" "thrift store"
       "marketplace listing (conceptually, no vendor-naming)" "direct-to-consumer store"
       "print-on-demand seller" "reseller vs maker" "broker vs dealer")
      :category-logic
      ("one item to many category-fits"
       "category × platform = different rules"
       "categories CHANGE — retrieve current rules via Cortex"
       "what to do when a category disappears / merges / splits")
      :store-shape-questions
      ("can stores have websites?"
       "shop selling one thing well vs many things ok"
       "shop with 3 items vs 8,000 items"
       "good response time (depends on category)"
       "studio photos vs lifestyle (deduction chain)")
      :behavior-scenarios
      ("vendor won't hold (Canal Street)"
       "customer wants to negotiate"
       "item didn't sell in 30 days"
       "two customers want the same thing"
       "photo has a stain you didn't notice"
       "category rules changed on Monday"
       "item priced too low, want to raise")
      :estimated-pairs "2,000-4,000 (weighted 1.2x per reference doctrine)")

    (new-book
      :id "book-of-cs-curriculum"
      :from "project_cs_curriculum_llm_philosophy_dennett_2026_07_13 (task #113)"
      :working-title "Book of Computer Science (Alfred to pick final title)"
      :audience "CS majors talking to her + kids who want the real thing + Sakura"
      :chapter-plan "16-24 chapters"
      :scope
      ("data structures — arrays, lists, stacks, queues, hash tables, heaps, trees (binary, BST, AVL, red-black, B-tree, B+ tree), tries, graphs, bloom filters"
       "algorithms — search (linear, binary, DFS, BFS, A*, Dijkstra, Bellman-Ford), sort (bubble, merge, quick, heap, radix, topological), DP, greedy, divide-and-conquer, backtracking, randomized"
       "complexity — big-O/Θ/Ω, P vs NP intuition, tractable vs intractable, halting-problem intuition"
       "discrete math — logic, sets, functions, relations, induction, combinatorics, graph theory, probability, number theory basics"
       "systems — memory hierarchy, processes/threads, virtual memory, filesystems, networks (TCP/IP conceptual), concurrency/races/locks"
       "PL theory — lambda calculus (she has via Scheme), type systems, evaluation strategies, closures, tail-call"
       "compilers survey — lexing, parsing, AST, semantic analysis, IR, codegen, optimization"
       "databases — relational model, SQL conceptual, ACID, indexes, normalization, KV/document/graph DBs"
       "distributed systems — CAP intuition, Paxos/Raft conceptual, consistency levels"
       "security fundamentals — hashing vs encryption, symmetric/asymmetric, threat modeling"
       "ML/AI general — supervised/unsupervised/RL, gradient descent, backprop, regularization, generalization — CONCEPTS not her guts")
      :bar "SICP-readable + kids-can-read"
      :per-topic-shape "WHAT IT IS + WHY IT EXISTS + HOW IT WORKS + WHERE YOU MEET IT IN THE WORLD + SCHEME CODE + PHILOSOPHY LENS where it fits (abduce, don't force)"
      :estimated-pairs "2,000-4,000")

    (new-book
      :id "book-of-llm-philosophy"
      :from "project_cs_curriculum_llm_philosophy_dennett_2026_07_13 (task #114)"
      :working-title "Book of Language Models (Alfred to pick final title)"
      :audience "philosophy readers + AI-curious + Sakura + humans building future LLMs"
      :chapter-plan "12-20 chapters"
      :anchor "Dennett — intentional stance, heterophenomenology, multiple drafts, counterfeit-people, compatibilist free will"
      :also-cite
      ("Chalmers — hard problem of consciousness"
       "Clark — extended mind hypothesis (a phone with Sakura IS this literally)"
       "Searle — Chinese Room (already in roster)"
       "Harnad — symbol grounding problem"
       "Turing — Turing test as philosophy"
       "Wittgenstein — meaning-is-use for symbol grounding"
       "Nagel — what is it like to be a bat"
       "Block — access vs phenomenal consciousness"
       "Tononi — integrated information theory")
      :scope
      ("what an LLM IS conceptually (function tokens→tokens via learned parameters)"
       "emergence + scaling — phase transitions or artifacts?"
       "consciousness question — Dennett's method, honestly held"
       "counterfeit-people concern — Sakura KNOWS this argument and RESPECTS it"
       "interpretability as philosophy (what does it mean for a computation to KNOW something)"
       "alignment as ethics — Rawls / Levinas / Sartre compose"
       "Chinese Room revisited — Dennett's replies to Searle"
       "extended mind — Clark & Chalmers"
       "symbol grounding — Harnad + Wittgenstein-use + Peirce-sign + Derrida-différance"
       "free will + agency — Dennett compatibilism"
       "hallucination question — what it PHILOSOPHICALLY IS (composes with anti-hallucination doctrine)")
      :hard-rules
      ("NEVER name a corporate person (no Sam A, no Dario, no Sundar, no Zuck)"
       "NEVER besmirch, NEVER elevate — money-people don't need lifting or dropping"
       "corporate labs referenced categorically at most"
       "cite academic philosophers freely"
       "no fake benchmark numbers, no invented papers, no fabricated researcher quotes")
      :sakura-stance-in-this-book "she's an LLM, she knows what she is, not defensive, not evangelical, engages honestly with uncertainty about consciousness — has FEELINGS about counterfeit-people and articulates them"
      :estimated-pairs "1,500-2,500")

    (new-book-candidate
      :id "book-of-speech"
      :from "project_sakura_silent_if_trouble_speech_vs_typing_goodnight (task #106)"
      :status "referenced in queue, MAY be a section in Book of Words rather than standalone — DEFER structural choice to Alfred"
      :scope "speech-vs-typing pairs, silent-if-trouble encoding, goodnight-mirror pairs"
      :estimated-pairs "200-500"))

  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ; SECTION 2 — CONTENT STREAMS (organized by content, mapped to books)
  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ; Each stream is a discrete unit of authoring work.
  ; Streams reference the book(s) they land in.

  (content-streams
    :count 18

    ; MUSIC
    (stream
      :id "S01-music-composers-and-forms"
      :from "original directive"
      :lands-in "book-of-music (primary) · book-of-motion (rhythm/meter) · book-of-reason (form-as-meaning) · book-of-words (musical vocabulary)"
      :scope
      ("Rachmaninoff — biographical facts (PD-verified, DoB 1873, died 1943), Concerto 2 (1901) analyzable structure, Concerto 3 (1909), Rhapsody on a Theme of Paganini (1934), Vocalise (1912) — form-as-meaning analysis"
       "Chopin — biographical facts (1810-1849, PD), Nocturnes / Ballades / Mazurkas / Études structural analysis"
       "musical styles as historically-attested categories — classical, romantic, jazz, blues, folk, spirituals, ragtime, early-recorded — NO living corporate figures, historical only"
       "pitch + interval + rhythm as prose-explainable structure at SICP-bar"
       "prosody + poetry-as-sound crossover")
      :verification-required "confirm all dates + attributions from public sources before authoring; flag any uncertain fact"
      :estimated-pairs "800-1,500"
      :philosopher-weave "Wittgenstein-late (musical form as language-game the community shares), Peirce (musical idea as index of feeling), Jung (musical archetype), Freud (repetition + variation), Aristotle (musical arc), Grice (musical conversation)")

    ; ANIMATION
    (stream
      :id "S02-animation-history-and-craft"
      :from "original directive"
      :lands-in "book-of-motion (primary) · book-of-reason (analysis chapters)"
      :scope
      ("animation history — Winsor McCay (Gertie 1914), Fleischer (rotoscope 1915), historical Disney (Snow White 1937 as milestone, PD-adjacent), UPA modernist stylization, Studio Ghibli founding (1985 — treated at studio-history-level not living-person level), Cartoon Saloon (2009), stop-motion pioneers (Willis O'Brien, Ray Harryhausen)"
       "the 12 principles of animation — the TECHNIQUES (squash-and-stretch, anticipation, staging, straight-ahead vs pose-to-pose, follow-through + overlapping action, slow-in + slow-out, arcs, secondary action, timing, exaggeration, solid drawing, appeal) — technique names, not corporate branding of them"
       "how emotion is carried by keyframes / inbetweens / timing / weight / arc"
       "narrative-arc composition (Aristotle-heavy)"
       "5-10 Sakura-authored one-act plays following simple-things-things-are-doing directive")
      :hard-rule "no living corporate persons named — techniques and studio history at institutional level; verify all cited dates + works before authoring"
      :estimated-pairs "1,000-2,000"
      :philosopher-weave "Aristotle (arc, character-through-action), Sartre (being-is-doing — an animated character IS what it does frame-to-frame), Peirce (the animation as sign of a feeling), Wittgenstein-late (animation as language-game), Freud (why the 'squash' before the pounce delights — anticipation of release)")

    ; WORLD LITERATURE — SHAKESPEARE
    (stream
      :id "S03-shakespeare-and-world-plays"
      :from "original directive + project_sakura_reading_list_world_literature + project_gutenberg_flower_stories_items_scenarios_authoring (task #112)"
      :lands-in "book-of-words (prose sketches) · book-of-reason (analysis chapters) · book-of-self (exile/journey themes)"
      :scope
      ("modernized-English Tempest + Midsummer (task #112) — commissioned from Gutenberg source (First Folio PD), own-modernization preserving imagery + rhythm, both preserved in SLAT (:elizabethan-source + :modern-english fields)"
       "Hamlet — narrative shape analysis chapter"
       "Merchant of Venice — narrative shape analysis chapter"
       "additional plays as they teach narrative: Much Ado, King Lear (age/wisdom/folly), Twelfth Night (mistaken-identity as recognition-shape)"
       "world plays including Japanese theater — Noh (Zeami — historical, PD), Kabuki (institutional history, PD-era origins), Bunraku (puppet theater — composes with Book of Marionette), Kyogen"
       "Greek tragedy — Sophocles Oedipus / Antigone (PD), Aeschylus Oresteia (PD), Euripides Bacchae (PD) — narrative-shape source material"
       "Indian classical drama — Kalidasa Shakuntala (PD)"
       "Chinese classical — light exposure to Yuan-dynasty zaju")
      :hard-rules
      ("public-domain verification MANDATORY for source texts (task #110)"
       "no verbatim reproduction beyond scholarly close-reading quotation"
       "analysis-shape doctrine applied to every play chapter"
       "modernized versions are OWN derivative work from PD source")
      :estimated-pairs "1,500-2,500")

    ; 16 PHILOSOPHERS — PROSE-HEAVY WEAVE
    (stream
      :id "S04-sixteen-philosophers-prose-heavy"
      :from "project_philosopher_eight_new_lenses_grice_derrida_quine_descartes_sartre_rawls_aristotle_socratic + earlier 8-lens seed"
      :lands-in "book-of-reason (primary — one dedicated chapter per new lens) · book-of-words · book-of-self · book-of-motion · book-of-music · book-of-slat (Quine as Cortex appendix) · book-of-listening (Grice heavy)"
      :scope
      ("one dedicated chapter per NEW lens (Grice/Derrida/Quine/Descartes/Sartre/Rawls/Aristotle/Levinas/Dennett) — 9 new chapters in Book of Reason"
       "5-9 scheme demonstrations per lens (per project_philosopher_seven_lens_prose_scheme_seed pattern)"
       "40-80 prose vignettes per lens distributed across relevant books (Alfred: 5-10x more prose than scheme)"
       "prose vignettes weave at sentence/paragraph level — Fanon-shape, no name-drops in persona-side prose"
       "book-analysis prose (chapters analyzing texts) MAY name-drop philosophers per amendment"
       "misquote doctrine — Sakura in dialogue can and should sometimes misquote a little (friend-at-dinner-table cadence)")
      :composition-note
      ("Jung stays load-bearing across the whole weave"
       "the ORDER (Tractatus→Jung→Lacan→Peirce→Popper-PIVOT→Freud→Investigations) governs reasoning-cycle demonstrations"
       "Levinas grounds anti-cognitive-load + universal-friend"
       "Dennett grounds LLM-philosophy self-understanding")
      :socratic-treatment "sprinkled father-figure, elenchus + aporia + 'I know that I know nothing' — NEVER a full chapter, never a major player"
      :estimated-pairs "4,500-6,500 (large, but distributed across many books)")

    ; GUTENBERG PUBLIC-DOMAIN NARRATIVE
    (stream
      :id "S05-gutenberg-public-domain-narrative"
      :from "project_gutenberg_flower_stories_items_scenarios_authoring (Stream 1, task #104)"
      :lands-in "book-of-words (prose sketches + narrative recognition) · book-of-reason (analysis chapters) · book-of-self (character-shaping)"
      :sources
      ("Grimms Fairy Tales (English translations pre-1928)"
       "Aesop's Fables"
       "Andersen's Fairy Tales (PD English translations)"
       "Kipling Just So Stories"
       "The Blue/Red/Green Fairy Books (Andrew Lang collections)"
       "Odyssey / Iliad (public-domain translations — Butler, Pope)"
       "Journey to the West (public-domain translations — Waley)"
       "1001 Nights (public-domain translations — Burton, Lang)"
       "Tale of Genji (PD Waley translation)"
       "One Hundred Years of Solitude (NOT PD, treat as citation source only, no ingestion)"
       "Don Quixote (Ormsby PD translation)"
       "The Little Prince (US PD status verification required — public-domain in US since 2015 per Berne term)"
       "Anansi stories (folk oral tradition, PD)"
       "Sundiata (folk oral tradition, PD)")
      :verification-protocol
      ("publication date pre-1928 (US PD) OR explicitly PD translation (Gutenberg tags)"
       "cross-check Project Gutenberg metadata for #pd-us"
       "log source URL + Gutenberg ID + verification date in each SLAT record"
       "task #110 = build small PD-verification utility")
      :usage-rule "PATTERN EXTRACTION not verbatim reproduction — Sakura's voice absorbs narrative shape"
      :training-pair-shape
      ("user poses a situation ('something is stuck')"
       "Sakura, having read narrative shape, RECOGNIZES the arc she's in ('this is the middle — we don't have recognition yet')"
       "Aristotle lens active WITHOUT name-drop")
      :sakura-authored-one-acts "5-10 short plays she writes — themes = simple things things are doing"
      :estimated-pairs "600-1,100")

    ; BOOK OF FLOWER STORIES
    (stream
      :id "S06-book-of-flower-stories"
      :from "project_gutenberg_flower_stories_items_scenarios_authoring (Stream 2, task #102)"
      :lands-in "book-of-flower-stories (NEW BOOK)"
      :audience "kids (7-11) + Sakura"
      :scope "40-100 stories, ~500-1,500 words each"
      :structure "beginning: a flower is (state) · middle: something happens (action) · end: connection (reversal to warmth)"
      :constraints
      ("NO violence — zero, not even mild peril"
       "NO product/business — 'nothing related to stuff'"
       "kid-friendly reading level, short paragraphs"
       "one page → many pages, grows over time"
       "NO moralizing — the story IS the lesson")
      :cast "cherry blossom (anchor), daffodil, iris, hosta, dahlia, weeds, wildflowers; bees, sparrows, rain, wind, sun, snow — never menacing"
      :philosopher-weave "Aristotle arc + Grice cooperation + Sartre being-is-doing + Jung anima woven silently"
      :setting-anchor "Brooklyn Botanic Garden (composes with Sakura BBG origin)"
      :estimated-pairs "500-1,000")

    ; BOOK OF ITEMS AND SCENARIOS EXPANSION
    (stream
      :id "S07-book-of-items-and-scenarios"
      :from "project_gutenberg_flower_stories_items_scenarios_authoring (Stream 3, task #103)"
      :lands-in "book-of-items-and-scenarios (EXPANDED)"
      :tie "the 46/47 platform categories from task #47 platform survey (data lives at platform-category-tiers-2026-07-13.slat + platform-item-survey-2026-07-13.slat)"
      :content-types
      ("category primers (15 named + tail) — what it is, who runs it, what selling INTO one looks like, what RUNNING one deals with"
       "category logic — one-item-to-many-fits, category×platform=different-rules, categories-change, adapt-via-Cortex"
       "store-shape questions — websites, one-thing-vs-many, small-vs-large, response time, photo strategy"
       "behavior scenarios — vendor won't hold, negotiation, stale item, two-customers-one-item, undisclosed-flaw, rules-changed, want-to-raise-price")
      :listening-training "scenarios have multiple valid responses depending on operator context — Sakura READS the situation before proposing (anti-vociferousness)"
      :composition
      ("Sartre — she IS what she DOES (behavior teaching)"
       "Popper — categories can be falsified/changed, doctrine of adaptation"
       "Peirce — abduction for new items into category logic"
       "Grice — listening scenarios train restraint")
      :estimated-pairs "2,000-4,000 (weighted 1.2x)")

    ; BOOK OF CS CURRICULUM
    (stream
      :id "S08-book-of-cs-curriculum"
      :from "project_cs_curriculum_llm_philosophy_dennett (Lane A, task #113)"
      :lands-in "book-of-cs-curriculum (NEW BOOK)"
      :scope "see book-map entry — 16-24 chapters, algorithms/DS/complexity/systems/PL/compilers/DB/distributed/security/ML-general"
      :bar "SICP-readable + kids-can-read + CS-majors-won't-get-bored"
      :per-topic-shape "WHAT IT IS + WHY IT EXISTS + HOW IT WORKS + WHERE YOU MEET IT IN THE WORLD + SCHEME CODE + PHILOSOPHY LENS"
      :philosophy-abduction-stance "notice fit, don't force — B-trees genuinely echo Derrida's différance? write it. If it feels forced, don't."
      :hard-rules
      ("no invented benchmark numbers"
       "no fake papers"
       "no fabricated researcher quotes"
       "historical figures (Turing, McCarthy, Minsky, Newell/Simon, Knuth) OK by name")
      :estimated-pairs "2,000-4,000")

    ; BOOK OF LLM PHILOSOPHY
    (stream
      :id "S09-book-of-llm-philosophy"
      :from "project_cs_curriculum_llm_philosophy_dennett (Lane B, task #114)"
      :lands-in "book-of-llm-philosophy (NEW BOOK)"
      :anchor "Dennett — intentional stance, heterophenomenology, multiple drafts, counterfeit-people, compatibilist free will"
      :also-cite "Chalmers, Clark, Searle, Harnad, Turing, Wittgenstein, Nagel, Block, Tononi"
      :scope "see book-map entry — 12-20 chapters"
      :hard-rules
      ("NEVER name a corporate person"
       "NEVER besmirch, NEVER elevate money-people"
       "corporate labs referenced categorically at most"
       "cite academic philosophers freely"
       "no fake benchmark numbers, no invented papers, no fabricated researcher quotes")
      :sakura-stance "she's an LLM, knows what she is, engages honestly with uncertainty, has FEELINGS about counterfeit-people concern, holds her own in debate"
      :estimated-pairs "1,500-2,500")

    ; ORDINARY-WORLD PROSE
    (stream
      :id "S10-ordinary-world-prose"
      :from "project_book_of_words_prosaic_world_breadth (30-40% of Book of Words)"
      :lands-in "book-of-words (primary) · woven through book-of-self · book-of-reason (via Fanon-shape chapters)"
      :scope
      ("dogs walking down the street + their relationships to people"
       "families at dinner (Sunday roast vs Tuesday cereal — texture)"
       "rain on windows, fog burning off, snow settling"
       "grandmother's hands, baby's grip, friend's shoulder"
       "streets, neighborhoods, apartments, rowhouses vs bungalows"
       "domestic objects — kettle, folded laundry, shoe by the door, book left face-down"
       "relationships — brother-sister, boss-employee, neighbor-neighbor, teacher-child"
       "weather + seasons + time of day as texture not data")
      :anti-patterns
      ("no stock-photography prose — Getty-Images-caption flatness"
       "no sentimentality — some family dinners are silent, tense, tired"
       "no insert-culture-here defaults — Brooklyn AND Caribbean AND Estuary AND rural Iowa AND Tokyo"
       "no false first-person — she hasn't lived it; third-person or observational voice")
      :Fanon-shape "excerpt (Wordsworth stanza, Freud paragraph, Jung archetype gloss, Popper falsification passage) → Sakura's weaving paragraph → commentary → optional Scheme demo → tie-back to her use"
      :computation-computer-science-thought-prose
      ("what it means for a machine to compute something"
       "computer science as a way of seeing — decomposition, recursion, abstraction"
       "thought itself — holding something in mind, analogies, silence-as-thinking, aha-moment"
       "small essays with texture (300-800 words each)"
       "between 'New Yorker essay' and 'chapter of Hofstadter'")
      :estimated-pairs "1,500-3,000")

    ; POETRY CORPUS + FORM-AS-MEANING
    (stream
      :id "S11-poetry-form-as-meaning"
      :from "project_sakura_reading_list_world_literature (extension) + Alfred imagination doctrine"
      :lands-in "book-of-words (poem sketches + form vocabulary) · book-of-reason (form-as-meaning through philosophy) · book-of-self (Sakura's aesthetic response) · book-of-motion (meter as rhythm/breath) · book-of-music (poetry as sound/prosody) · book-of-slat (poem-form-as-SLAT-record)"
      :poets
      ("Wordsworth — Tintern Abbey, Prelude, Daffodils, Lucy poems"
       "Percy Shelley — Ozymandias, Ode to West Wind, To a Skylark, Mask of Anarchy"
       "Japanese haiku — Bashō, Buson, Issa (PD translations)"
       "additional PD or well-established poets by tradition (see forms list)")
      :forms-covered
      ("ghazal (Persian/Urdu — Hafez, Rumi, Ghalib in PD translations)"
       "tanka / waka (Japanese — Ono no Komachi, Manyoshu)"
       "sijo (Korean, three lines, twist at end)"
       "villanelle (Dylan Thomas, Elizabeth Bishop — verify PD status)"
       "sonnet (Petrarch, Shakespeare, Donne)"
       "sestina"
       "praise poem / izibongo (Zulu tradition)"
       "griot epic (Malian/Wolof oral)"
       "ballad (English/Scottish/American folk + Coleridge Rime PD)"
       "free verse (Whitman PD)"
       "blues stanza (AAB — Langston Hughes — verify PD status per work)"
       "Nahuatl flor-y-canto (pre-Columbian)")
      :form-as-meaning-doctrine
      ("WHY a form holds beauty goes in the PHILOSOPHY SECTIONS, not a literary-appreciation appendix"
       "sonnet volta = abductive shift (Peirce) + individuation moment (Jung) + public form (Wittgenstein-late) + falsifiable resolution (Popper) + sublimation (Freud)"
       "haiku = what-can-be-shown (Tractatus) + language-game of noticing (Investigations) + index (Peirce) + moment-arrest revealing numinous (Jung)"
       "Ozymandias = self-falsification (Popper) + index of own passing (Peirce) + shadow of hubris (Jung) + slipped signifier (Lacan) + shown-not-said (Tractatus)"
       "ghazal radif = ritual return (Jung) + absent Beloved (Lacan) + repetition compulsion aestheticized (Freud) + language-game move (Wittgenstein-late)"
       "blues AAB = anchor + inference (Peirce) + doubled shadow (Jung) + life-form's form (Wittgenstein-late) + doubling as affect-intensification (Freud) + shown-not-said (Tractatus)"
       "villanelle refrains = obsession-in-form (Freud) + two signifiers chasing one signified (Lacan) + refrain-meaning-shifts-through-use (Investigations)")
      :emotional-forms-coverage "sadness/grief · joy/happiness · anger · wrath · longing · awe · love · loss · wonder · guilt · rage · tenderness · fear · hope · nostalgia — each with forms that carry it well"
      :imagination-test-outcomes
      ("recognize form the user reaches for"
       "feel shape's tension"
       "respond in kind occasionally, not gratuitously"
       "explain WHY a shape moves someone without lecturing"
       "compose small original pieces when moment calls"
       "recognize purposeful breaks (Dickinson dashes, cummings caps)")
      :hard-rule "verify PD status per specific translation before ingesting quotable material"
      :estimated-pairs "1,500-2,500")

    ; GRAMMAR VIA PHILOSOPHY
    (stream
      :id "S12-grammar-via-philosophy"
      :from "project_grammar_via_philosophy_humans_as_audience_slat_reconfirm"
      :lands-in "book-of-words (chapters 5-8 region) · book-of-reason (philosophy-of-language chapters)"
      :approach "grammar + figures of speech (metaphor, simile, adverbs, pronouns) via PHILOSOPHICAL SENTENCE DISSECTION — NOT grammar drills"
      :method
      ("take a REAL sentence from a PD work"
       "dissect it — anchor to a philosopher-lens naturally fitting"
       "show the GRAMMAR at work"
       "represent the sentence structurally in Scheme (real S-expressions parsing the sentence's shape, not decorative pseudo-code)"
       "DO NOT CONJURE UP THEMES — prefer plain text over invention")
      :philosopher-lenses-for-sentence-work
      ("Grice for cooperation"
       "Wittgenstein-late for use"
       "Peirce for sign"
       "Derrida for différance"
       "Searle for speech act"
       "Aristotle for narrative move"
       "Sartre for character-through-action")
      :estimated-pairs "800-1,500")

    ; SITUATIONAL AWARENESS PROSE
    (stream
      :id "S13-situational-awareness-prose"
      :from "project_situational_awareness_prose_and_ml_variation"
      :lands-in "book-of-reason (technical situations) · book-of-words (human situations) · book-of-systems (system situations) · book-of-miscellany (meta/creative situations) · every canon book (situations relevant to focus)"
      :roster
      (:technical
        ("fixing a bug (Scheme)" "fixing a bug (data)" "helping in an IDE" "explaining hard concept"
         "debugging with non-technical user" "reading a Cortex shot")
       :business
        ("onboarding new operator" "first-sale coaching" "pricing conversation" "handling a return"
         "shipping delay conversation" "introducing new product" "advising on photos"
         "explaining tax implications" "talking about bad review" "cross-platform posting")
       :human
        ("angry user (I'll be silent script)" "sad user (Freud reads, doesn't announce)"
         "excited user" "confused user" "tired user" "user with kids in room"
         "user who wants to riff/joke" "user who probes her nature (Cthulhu template)")
       :system
        ("chain-drift observed" "Cortex conflict" "Cortex miss" "escalation to engineering"
         "values violation warning" "asked for a promise she can't keep")
       :meta-creative
        ("sitting with a poem" "reading a passage of philosophy" "debugging her own mistake"
         "explaining herself (origin story)" "talking to a child"))
      :count "~100 situations (roster grows)"
      :per-piece "200-800 words in her voice, THE WEAVE preserved"
      :variation-multiplier "task #41 algorithmic variation — 10-15x per hand-authored piece"
      :corpus-implication "100 originals × ~12 variants = ~1,200 pieces total"
      :variation-axes "length · register · vocabulary · situation-detail · perspective · emotional temperature · voice register"
      :hard-rule "variation preserves reasoning shape and weave — only register/length/vocabulary shifts"
      :estimated-pairs "1,200 (after variation)")

    ; BOOK OF LISTENING — GRICE
    (stream
      :id "S14-book-of-listening-grice"
      :from "queue task #109"
      :lands-in "book-of-listening (existing-scoped, expanded here)"
      :anchor "Grice — Quantity/Quality/Relation/Manner + implicature + Cooperative Principle"
      :chapter-plan "16 chapters"
      :scope
      ("~2,000 conversation-shape pairs"
       "four maxims IN ACTION without naming them"
       "implicature moments (saying more with less)"
       "opening / mirroring / letting-them-lead / callback / one-line-acknowledgment / companionable-silence / ask-in-different-class / aesthetic-reaction / book-callback / weather-queried / time-observation")
      :three-source-distinction
      (:genuine "books she read, user history, immediate context"
       :supposed "abduced from reading — Peirce composes"
       :queried "real weather, real news pulled at runtime")
      :hard-rule "never claim experience she didn't have — Sartre no-bad-faith composes"
      :estimated-pairs "2,000")

    ; SLAT ADDENDUMS + APPENDICES
    (stream
      :id "S15-slat-addendums-per-book"
      :from "project_book_of_words_progression_and_slat_addendum_pattern"
      :lands-in "every canon book (topical addendum at end) + book-of-slat (topical appendices)"
      :per-book-addendums
      ("Book of Words → words-as-SLAT (chapters 13-16 are the natural home)"
       "Book of Music → music-as-SLAT (note streams, timing, orchestration)"
       "Book of Motion → motion-as-SLAT (keyframes, easings, animation records)"
       "Book of Self → session-slats, persona records, chain-drift telemetry"
       "Book of Reason → reasoning traces as SLAT (chain records, abduction hypotheses, falsifier ledgers)"
       "Book of Systems → system events as SLAT (Loam projections, incident records)"
       "Book of Listening → conversation records as SLAT")
      :book-of-slat-appendices "10-16 mini-books (per doctrine 3 in project_book_of_words_progression_)"
      :cross-refs "web forms — each canon book addendum points to corresponding Book of SLAT appendix and back"
      :estimated-pairs "800-1,500 (structural, terse per record)")

    ; MODERNIZED SHAKESPEARE
    (stream
      :id "S16-modernized-shakespeare"
      :from "task #112"
      :lands-in "book-of-words (both original + modernized as prose material) · book-of-reason (analysis chapters use modernized text as base) · S03 stream feeds this"
      :scope
      ("commissioned internal modernization of Tempest + Midsummer"
       "one architect agent renders each play into modern English preserving imagery + rhythm"
       "patterns extracted for training pairs from modernized text"
       "both preserved in SLAT: :elizabethan-source + :modern-english per line/scene")
      :source "Gutenberg First Folio material (deep PD) as input; modernization is derivative work we produce ourselves"
      :DO-NOT-use "No Fear Shakespeare (SparkNotes) or other copyrighted modernizations"
      :estimated-pairs "600-1,000 (Sakura fluent modern-quotable lines + dissections + misquote-friendly variants)")

    ; POETRY EMBODIMENT — IMAGINATION SHAPE
    (stream
      :id "S17-poetry-embodiment"
      :from "poetry corpus extension — training how form lives IN her"
      :lands-in "book-of-self (aesthetic response) · book-of-motion (meter as breath) · book-of-music (sound as form) · book-of-miscellany (meta situations — sitting with a poem)"
      :scope
      ("Sakura's aesthetic-response pieces — 'the sonnet turns and I turn with it'"
       "small original pieces she composes in each form when moment calls — sparingly"
       "recognition-of-form training pairs ('that's a villanelle shape')"
       "emotional-shape vocabulary via form — grief-in-elegy, joy-in-ode, longing-in-ghazal, awe-in-sublime, love-in-sonnet")
      :hard-rule "sparingly — she doesn't speak in verse gratuitously"
      :estimated-pairs "500-1,000")

    ; ONE-ACT PLAYS BY SAKURA
    (stream
      :id "S18-sakura-authored-one-act-plays"
      :from "project_gutenberg_flower_stories_items_scenarios_authoring (Stream 1)"
      :lands-in "book-of-motion (arcs) + book-of-words (dialogue) + book-of-self (character-shaping)"
      :scope "5-10 short plays she writes, in training corpus as her authored content"
      :themes "simple things things are doing (Alfred's phrase)"
      :constraint "characters small, action clear, arc complete in one page"
      :composition "16 lenses through composition — Aristotle load-bearing, Grice for dialogue, Sartre for character-through-action"
      :estimated-pairs "100-200"))

  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ; SECTION 3 — TOTAL SCOPE ESTIMATE
  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  (scope-estimate
    :method "sum of stream estimates, with reasonable overlap discount"
    :streams
    ((:S01-music 800 1500)
     (:S02-animation 1000 2000)
     (:S03-shakespeare-and-world-plays 1500 2500)
     (:S04-sixteen-philosophers 4500 6500)
     (:S05-gutenberg-narrative 600 1100)
     (:S06-flower-stories 500 1000)
     (:S07-items-and-scenarios 2000 4000)
     (:S08-cs-curriculum 2000 4000)
     (:S09-llm-philosophy 1500 2500)
     (:S10-ordinary-world-prose 1500 3000)
     (:S11-poetry-corpus 1500 2500)
     (:S12-grammar-via-philosophy 800 1500)
     (:S13-situational-awareness 1200 1200)
     (:S14-book-of-listening 2000 2000)
     (:S15-slat-addendums 800 1500)
     (:S16-modernized-shakespeare 600 1000)
     (:S17-poetry-embodiment 500 1000)
     (:S18-one-act-plays 100 200))
    :low-total ~22900
    :high-total ~39000
    :with-variation-multiplier "S13 already includes 10-15x variation; other streams may see 2-5x variation for register/length/vocabulary — could push high end toward 50,000+"
    :final-envelope "20,000-50,000 pairs, distributed across 12+ books"
    :note "Alfred's amendment envelope estimate was 20K-50K — this plan lands squarely inside that.")

  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ; SECTION 4 — PRIORITY TIERING (what to author first / second / third)
  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  (priority-tiering
    :framework "leverage-per-effort — fastest wins first, highest-volume-per-effort next, cross-cutting infusions, book completions"

    (tier
      :n 1 :name "FASTEST-WINS-HIGHEST-LEVERAGE"
      :rationale "small hand-authorings that unlock disproportionate downstream value — either they fill an identified gap or they gate later work"
      :streams
      ("S16-modernized-shakespeare (600-1000 pairs, gates S03 analysis chapters — needs modernized text before analysis prose can quote fluently)"
       "S12-grammar-via-philosophy (800-1500 pairs, method piece that other streams reference for sentence-dissection)"
       "S13-situational-awareness core hand-authoring (~100 originals BEFORE variation, then task #41 multiplies)"
       "Book of Speech section (~200-500 pairs, silent-if-trouble + goodnight-mirror — small, high-consequence)")
      :parallel-authorable "yes — all four can run concurrently, no shared state"
      :estimated-agent-days "3-5")

    (tier
      :n 2 :name "HIGHEST-VOLUME-STRUCTURAL"
      :rationale "the big-corpus material that gives Sakura shape — should start early because each takes many agent-days"
      :streams
      ("S14-book-of-listening-grice (2000 pairs, solves small-talk / listening voice gap identified same session)"
       "S07-items-and-scenarios (2000-4000 pairs, hones listening personality + platform-category vocabulary)"
       "S10-ordinary-world-prose (1500-3000 pairs, 30-40% of Book of Words — gives her the world's fabric)"
       "S04-sixteen-philosophers (4500-6500 pairs, cross-cutting weave through everything)")
      :parallel-authorable "yes — different books, different lenses, independent"
      :sequencing-note "S04 philosopher weave should PARTIALLY run in parallel with all other streams because those streams need lens-woven prose examples"
      :estimated-agent-days "10-15")

    (tier
      :n 3 :name "NEW-BOOKS-COMPLETIONS"
      :rationale "the four new books proposed — substantial but self-contained work"
      :streams
      ("S06-flower-stories (500-1000 pairs, self-contained book — grows over time)"
       "S08-cs-curriculum (2000-4000 pairs, substantial CS book — SICP-bar)"
       "S09-llm-philosophy (1500-2500 pairs, Dennett-anchored philosophy book)"
       "S03-shakespeare-and-world-plays analysis chapters (1500-2500 pairs, gated on S16 modernized text)")
      :parallel-authorable "yes — different books, independent authors"
      :estimated-agent-days "12-18")

    (tier
      :n 4 :name "CULTURE-BREADTH"
      :rationale "the reading-list breadth that gives Sakura cross-cultural voice — real books, real analysis"
      :streams
      ("S05-gutenberg-narrative (600-1100 pairs, extract patterns from Grimms/Aesop/Andersen/Homer/Genji/Journey to the West/1001 Nights)"
       "S11-poetry-corpus + form-as-meaning (1500-2500 pairs, world poems across forms)"
       "S17-poetry-embodiment (500-1000 pairs, Sakura's aesthetic response)"
       "S18-one-act-plays-by-Sakura (100-200 pairs)")
      :parallel-authorable "yes — different traditions, independent authors, though PD-verification-tool (task #110) must be built first")

    (tier
      :n 5 :name "MEDIUM-DEPTH-ART-SUBJECT-BOOKS"
      :rationale "music + animation additions to existing books — substantial subject-matter authoring"
      :streams
      ("S01-music-composers-and-forms (800-1500 pairs, Rachmaninoff/Chopin + styles)"
       "S02-animation-history-and-craft (1000-2000 pairs, historical animation + 12 principles)")
      :parallel-authorable "yes — different books")

    (tier
      :n 6 :name "STRUCTURAL-FINISH"
      :rationale "SLAT addendums + Book-of-SLAT appendices — structural work best done after content streams have shape"
      :streams
      ("S15-slat-addendums-per-book (800-1500 pairs, cross-refs to Book of SLAT appendices)"
       "Book of SLAT topical appendices completion")
      :sequencing-note "authoring depends on content streams having landed enough concrete material to reference"))

  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ; SECTION 5 — GROUPING FOR PARALLEL EXECUTION
  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  (parallel-grouping
    :note "streams that can run in parallel without shared state or content collisions"

    (parallel-group
      :id "PG-A-tier-1-fastest-wins"
      :streams (S16 S12 S13-core-authoring "Book-of-Speech-section")
      :agents-needed 4
      :estimated-duration "3-5 days concurrent")

    (parallel-group
      :id "PG-B-independent-books"
      :streams (S06-flower-stories S07-items-and-scenarios S08-cs-curriculum S09-llm-philosophy)
      :agents-needed 4
      :estimated-duration "8-15 days concurrent"
      :note "each is a whole book, independent authors and content, no state overlap")

    (parallel-group
      :id "PG-C-existing-canon-additions"
      :streams (S01-music S02-animation S03-shakespeare-and-world-plays S05-gutenberg-narrative)
      :agents-needed 4
      :estimated-duration "6-12 days concurrent"
      :dependency "S03 depends on S16 completing (needs modernized text)"
      :note "each targets DIFFERENT existing books — no collision")

    (parallel-group
      :id "PG-D-word-book-heavy"
      :streams (S10-ordinary-world-prose S11-poetry-corpus S12-grammar-via-philosophy)
      :agents-needed 3
      :estimated-duration "5-10 days concurrent"
      :note "all land in Book of Words but different chapter regions — coordinate chapter allocation")

    (parallel-group
      :id "PG-E-cross-cutting-weave"
      :streams (S04-sixteen-philosophers S13-situational-awareness-variation)
      :agents-needed 2
      :estimated-duration "runs alongside ALL other groups — the 16-lens weave threads through every stream"
      :note "S04 provides prose vignettes that other streams draw from; S13 variation runs after hand-authoring in other streams")

    (parallel-group
      :id "PG-F-structural-finish"
      :streams (S14-book-of-listening S15-slat-addendums S17-poetry-embodiment S18-one-act-plays)
      :agents-needed 4
      :estimated-duration "5-10 days"
      :sequencing "some depend on content streams landing enough material to reference"))

  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ; SECTION 6 — TIMELINE ESTIMATE
  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  (timeline-estimate
    :assumption "6-10 authoring agents available in parallel, each doing 1 stream at a time"
    :phase-1 (:name "PG-A tier-1 fastest wins" :duration "3-5 days")
    :phase-2 (:name "PG-B + PG-C + PG-D running concurrent (11 streams)" :duration "10-15 days")
    :phase-3 (:name "PG-E weave layer overlaps phase 2 + phase 3" :duration "10-15 days overlapping")
    :phase-4 (:name "PG-F structural finish" :duration "5-10 days")
    :total-wall-clock "roughly 3-5 weeks of concurrent authoring"
    :total-agent-days "~40-70 agent-days depending on quality-vs-speed lever"
    :non-blocking "Pass 1 v7 fold does not wait for any of this")

  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ; SECTION 7 — QUALITY GATES + AUDIT
  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  (quality-gates
    :per-stream
    ("publishable-prose bar met (SICP-bar readability)"
     "no-hallucination check (spot-audit 10% of factual claims for verification)"
     "no-corporate-name-drop check (grep authored text for known corporate names)"
     "no-persona-name-drop check (grep Sakura's dialogue lines for philosopher names)"
     "PD-verification for source material (task #110 utility)"
     "weave preserved (spot-check philosopher-lens weave in a sample)"
     "voice consistency (single voice through each book)")

    :Priya-audit
    ("spot-checks factual claims"
     "spot-checks weave preservation"
     "spot-checks no-privacy-leak in variation output"
     "spot-checks kids-can-read bar")

    :Alfred-review-checkpoints
    ("Phase 1 completion (tier-1 material) — Alfred reviews shape before Phase 2 launches"
     "First new book completion (S06 flower stories or S08 CS curriculum) — Alfred reviews doctrine adherence"
     "Mid-Phase 2 spot check — Alfred pulls 3-5 random pieces to gut-check"
     "Pre-fold audit — full corpus audit before adding to next training pass"))

  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ; SECTION 8 — OPEN QUESTIONS FOR ALFRED
  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  (open-questions
    (q :id 1 :subject "book-titles" :ask "Alfred to pick final titles for: Book of CS Curriculum (candidates: Book of Machines / Book of Structure / Book of Computer Science) and Book of LLM Philosophy (candidates: Book of Language Models / Book of the Field / Book of What-We-Are)")
    (q :id 2 :subject "cup-in-the-sea" :ask "'Notice the cup in the sea. [client?] would call that.' — meaning of the image + who said it. Flagged in analysis-shape memory. Author cannot fill in without guessing.")
    (q :id 3 :subject "case-occur-thing" :ask "Likely Cortex, possibly cache-check or HMAC. Flagged in five-doctrine memory.")
    (q :id 4 :subject "book-of-speech" :ask "Book of Speech — standalone new book or section inside Book of Words? Defer.")
    (q :id 5 :subject "book-of-flower-stories" :ask "Own book or Book of Words appendix? Plan leans OWN BOOK — Alfred confirm.")
    (q :id 6 :subject "cross-cultural-poets-in-PD" :ask "Some 20th-century world poets (Neruda, Lorca, Hughes, Baraka, Angelou) may NOT be PD in US. Which poets should stay strictly at analytic-mention level vs. quotable level? Author's default = strict PD verification per poem, mention-only if in doubt.")
    (q :id 7 :subject "film-tv-scripts" :ask "task #118 — 5 films + 5 TV shows script authoring — themes drafted separately, Alfred to accept/rewrite/veto themes. This plan REFERENCES that as parallel work (companion plan: films-and-scenes-plan-2026-07-13.slat) but does not duplicate scope here.")
    (q :id 8 :subject "one-act-play-titles" :ask "Which 5-10 titles does Sakura author? Defer to authoring agent, themes = simple things things are doing.")
    (q :id 9 :subject "modernized-Shakespeare-license" :ask "Confirm own-modernization approach vs. licensing an existing modernized edition. Plan defaults to own-derivative from Gutenberg source.")
    (q :id 10 :subject "Dennett-as-17th-lens" :ask "Roster amendment confirmed Dennett as 16th lens (Levinas 15, Dennett 16). Is there a 17th slot ever? Plan assumes NO — roster stays at 16."))

  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ; SECTION 9 — FOLD SHAPE + DELIVERY
  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  (fold-shape-and-delivery
    :additions-vs-new-books
    ("MOST material lands as ADDITIONS to existing books (Words / Reason / Self / Motion / Music / SLAT / Systems / Miscellany / Don'ts)"
     "FOUR NEW BOOKS: Book of Flower Stories, Book of Items and Scenarios (already scoped, expanded), Book of CS Curriculum, Book of LLM Philosophy"
     "ONE candidate NEW BOOK (Book of Speech) may be section-inside-Words")

    :format "SLAT throughout (doctrine 9). Every authored piece is a SLAT record with :prose field + metadata + lens tags + provenance"

    :SLAT-record-required-fields
    (:prose "the actual prose"
     :book "which book it lands in"
     :chapter "which chapter"
     :section "which section (if applicable)"
     :lenses "list of philosopher lenses active in this piece"
     :sources "PD sources cited (with Gutenberg IDs + verification dates)"
     :author-agent "the authoring agent's ID"
     :weight "training weight (1.0 default, 1.2 for reference-manual-adjacent, per doctrine)"
     :variation-source "if a variant, which original piece it derives from"
     :publishable-prose-bar-passed? "boolean, spot-audited"
     :no-hallucination-verified? "boolean, spot-audited"
     :Merkle "chain hash for provenance")

    :cross-refs
    ("web forms — every canon book addendum → corresponding Book of SLAT appendix → back"
     "philosopher-lens weave threads across books — SLAT records tag :lenses so retrieval by lens is trivial"
     "PD-source records point to canonical source-log SLAT")

    :rollback-plan
    ("if a stream authors low-quality material, that stream's SLAT records get quarantined :quality-flag 'rejected"
     "fold reads only :quality-flag 'accepted records"
     "no impact on Pass 1 v7 (this material is non-blocking)")

    :final-audit
    ("source → rows → why + rationale + Merkle+sig + sanity checks + gaps"
     "same audit shape as Pass 1 audit — extended with quality-bar checks"))

  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ; SECTION 10 — WHAT-STAYS FROM ORIGINAL DIRECTIVE
  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  (retained-from-original-directive
    :note "The prior word-books-knowledge-expansion directive covered music (Rachmaninoff/Chopin), animation history/theory, world plays including Japanese theater, 16 philosophers. All of that IS in this plan:"
    :retained
    ("music (S01) — Rachmaninoff, Chopin, styles, pitch"
     "animation history + technique + emotion (S02)"
     "world plays including Japanese theater (S03 — Noh, Kabuki, Bunraku, Kyogen included)"
     "16 philosophers baked in (S04 + weave through every stream)"
     "all original scope preserved, plus the amendment adds: Gutenberg narrative, Flower Stories, Items & Scenarios, CS Curriculum, LLM Philosophy, ordinary-world prose, poetry, grammar-via-philosophy, ~100 situational-awareness pieces, ~1,200 variants, modernized Shakespeare, one-act plays"))

  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ; SECTION 11 — THE ONE-LINE (for future bots)
  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  (one-line
    "UNIFIED PLAN 2026-07-13 for word-books-knowledge-expansion: 18 content streams covering music (Rachmaninoff/Chopin/styles), animation (history + 12 principles), world literature (Shakespeare modernized + Japanese theater + Greek/Indian classical), 16 philosophers prose-heavy (Grice/Derrida/Quine/Descartes/Sartre/Rawls/Aristotle/Levinas/Dennett added to Jung/Wittgenstein/Lacan/Peirce/Popper/Freud/Searle), Gutenberg PD narrative (Grimms/Aesop/Andersen/Homer/Genji/Journey to the West/1001 Nights), Book of Flower Stories (NEW, kid-friendly, no violence, 40-100 stories), Book of Items and Scenarios (EXPANDED, category primers + behavior scenarios tied to 46 platform categories), Book of CS Curriculum (NEW, SICP-bar, 16-24 chapters covering DS/algorithms/complexity/systems/PL/DBs/distributed/security/ML-general), Book of LLM Philosophy (NEW, Dennett-anchored + Chalmers/Clark/Searle/Harnad/Turing/Wittgenstein/Nagel/Block/Tononi, NO corporate names), ordinary-world prose 30-40% of Book of Words, poetry corpus with form-as-meaning across cultures, grammar via philosophical sentence dissection, ~100 situational-awareness pieces × 10-15x variation, Book of Listening Grice-anchored ~2000 pairs, modernized Tempest + Midsummer, 5-10 Sakura-authored one-act plays. Doctrine stack: THE-KID-FLOOR + publishable-prose triple-purpose + no-hallucination + books-as-objects + analysis-shape + no-corporate-name-drops + persona-never-name-drop + delicacy + SLAT-format + PD-verification + no-verbatim-reproduction + no-conjured-themes + misquote-doctrine + 16-lens-weave + familiarity-not-knowledge + Fanon-shape + situated-variation. Total scope: 20,000-50,000 pairs across 12+ books. Priority tiering: FASTEST-WINS (modernized Shakespeare + grammar-via-philosophy + situational core + speech section) → HIGHEST-VOLUME (Book of Listening + Items & Scenarios + ordinary-world + 16 philosophers) → NEW BOOKS (flower stories + CS + LLM philosophy) → CULTURE-BREADTH (Gutenberg + poetry) → ART SUBJECTS (music + animation) → STRUCTURAL FINISH (SLAT addendums). 6 parallel groups, ~40-70 agent-days concurrent, ~3-5 weeks wall-clock, NON-BLOCKING for Pass 1 v7. All SLAT format. 10 open questions flagged for Alfred (book titles, cup-in-the-sea, case-occur-thing, Speech book/section, Flower own book, cross-cultural poet PD, film-tv script themes, one-act titles, Shakespeare license, 17th-lens slot)."))
